Appendix A: Detailed Derivation of Bayesian Update and Martingale Property

A.1 Hierarchical Bayesian Update (Proposition 1)

We restate the update rule for completeness. Given a belief b_t(i,\theta) = \mathbb{P}(I=i,\Theta=\theta \mid h_t) and a question q_t with response r_t, the posterior is

b_{t+1}(i,\theta) = \frac{b_t(i,\theta) \, P(r_t \mid q_t, i, \theta)}{\sum_{i',\theta'} b_t(i',\theta') \, P(r_t \mid q_t, i', \theta')}.

Derivation. By Bayes’ theorem,

\mathbb{P}(I=i,\Theta=\theta \mid h_t, q_t, r_t) = \frac{\mathbb{P}(I=i,\Theta=\theta \mid h_t, q_t) \, \mathbb{P}(r_t \mid I=i,\Theta=\theta, h_t, q_t)}{\sum_{i',\theta'} \mathbb{P}(I=i',\Theta=\theta' \mid h_t, q_t) \, \mathbb{P}(r_t \mid I=i',\Theta=\theta', h_t, q_t)}.

Since q_t is chosen based on h_t only, \mathbb{P}(I=i,\Theta=\theta \mid h_t, q_t) = \mathbb{P}(I=i,\Theta=\theta \mid h_t) = b_t(i,\theta). The response model assumes \mathbb{P}(r_t \mid I=i,\Theta=\theta, h_t, q_t) = P(r_t \mid q_t, i, \theta). Substituting yields the formula.

A.2 Martingale Property of the Belief Components

We show that for each fixed x = (i,\theta), the sequence \{b_t(x)\}_{t\ge 0} is a martingale with respect to the filtration \mathcal{F}_t = \sigma(h_t). Indeed,

\mathbb{E}[b_{t+1}(x) \mid \mathcal{F}_t] = \sum_{r} b_{t+1}(x) \, P(r \mid q_t, b_t).

Using the update rule,

\sum_r \frac{b_t(x) P(r \mid q_t, x)}{\sum_{x'} b_t(x') P(r \mid q_t, x')} \cdot P(r \mid q_t, b_t) = b_t(x) \sum_r \frac{P(r \mid q_t, x)}{\sum_{x'} b_t(x') P(r \mid q_t, x')} \cdot P(r \mid q_t, b_t).

But P(r \mid q_t, b_t) = \sum_{x'} b_t(x') P(r \mid q_t, x'). Hence the sum over r simplifies to b_t(x) \sum_r P(r \mid q_t, x) = b_t(x). The boundedness of b_t(x) in [0,1] guarantees the martingale convergence theorem applies.

